0submarine%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean.%3Cp%3EUS%20Naval%20History%20and%20Heritage%20Command%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20harrowing%20capture%20came%20the%20task%20of%20towing%20it%20back%20home.%20Operating%20under%20utmost%20secrecy%2C%20the%20US%20Navy%20painted%20the%20U-boat%20black%20and%20renamed%20it%20USS%20Nemo%20to%20hide%20its%20capture%20from%20the%20Germans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20partially%20submerged%20vessel%20was%20towed%20over%202%2C500%20nautical%20miles%20to%20Bermuda%20to%20study%20the%20submarine's%20technology%20and%20intelligence%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2058%20sailors%20from%20the%20U-505%20were%20transported%20and%20held%20at%20a%20prisoner-of-war%20camp%20in%20Louisiana%2C%20kept%20under%20special%20conditions%20like%20isolation%20and%20limited%20communication%20to%20keep%20the%20submarine's%20capture%20a%20secret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20remained%20at%20the%20camp%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20war%2C%20with%20the%20last%20of%20the%20captives%20repatriating%20back%20to%20Germany%20in%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EUncovering%20German%20secrets%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225689%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Detection%20and%20radio%20equipment%20on%20board%20the%20German%20submarine%20U-505.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6778401b59d276c1cdaffcd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224435%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDetection%20and%20radio%20equipment%20on%20board%20the%20German%20submarine%20U-505.%3Cp%3EUS%20Naval%20History%20and%20Heritage%20Command%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Navy%20recovered%20codebooks%2C%20thousands%20of%20communication%20documents%2C%20and%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falan-turing-enigma-code-nazi-world-war-2012-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnigma%20machines%3C%2Fa%3E%20used%20by%20the%20German%20military%C2%A0to%20decode%20and%20encrypt%20messages%20to%20and%20from%20the%20U-505.%20Breaking%20Enigma%20codes%20allowed%20fleet%20commands%20to%20know%20where%20U-boats%20would%20attack.%20That%2C%20along%20with%20increasing%20Allied%20aircraft%20patrols%20for%20submarines%2C%20turned%20the%20tide%20of%20the%20Battle%20of%20the%20Atlantic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20naval%20engineers%20uncovered%20that%20the%20Germans%20were%20developing%20an%20advanced%20acoustic-homing%20torpedo%20to%20target%20a%20ship's%20propellers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20intelligence%20also%20allowed%20the%20US%20to%20get%20more%20precise%20locations%20for%20German%20U-boat%20operations%2C%20redirecting%20merchant%20vessels%20from%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Task%20Group's%20brilliant%20achievement%20in%20disabling%2C%20capturing%2C%20and%20towing%20to%20a%20United%20States%20base%20a%20modern%20enemy%20man-of-war%20taken%20in%20combat%20on%20the%20high%20seas%20is%20a%20feat%20unprecedented%20in%20individual%20and%20group%20bravery%2C%20execution%2C%20and%20accomplishment%20in%20the%20Naval%20History%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20Ingersoll%20said%20in%20the%20presidential%20citation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPreserving%20the%20U-boat%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222820%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20enjoy%20a%20day%20at%20the%20beach%20near%20the%20captured%20German%20submarine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6778299c44aa267a51f22305%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221447%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20enjoy%20a%20day%20at%20the%20beach%20near%20the%20captured%20German%20submarine.%3Cp%3EGriffin%20Museum%20of%20Science%20and%20Industry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Navy%20learned%20what%20it%20could%20from%20the%20German%20submarine%2C%20the%20U-505%20was%20destined%20to%20become%20gunnery%20and%20torpedo%20target%20practice%2C%20a%20typical%20fate%20for%20captured%20enemy%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20after%20its%20capture%2C%20Chicago%20native%20John%20Gallery%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20Guadalcanal%20Capt.%20Gallery%2C%20contacted%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Chicago%20Museum%20of%20Science%20and%20Industry%20to%20preserve%20the%20wartime%20relic%20as%20an%20exhibit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Navy%20donated%20the%20U-boat%20to%20the%20museum%2C%20but%20the%20city%20of%20Chicago%20was%20tasked%20with%20raising%20%24250%2C000%20to%20move%2C%20install%2C%20and%20restore%20the%20submarine%20for%20exhibition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E'Submarine%20crossing'%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222298%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20U-505%20on%20the%20beach%20as%20workers%20move%20the%20vessel%20toward%20the%20museum.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6778299d9de00e389eb44c78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222859%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20U-505%20on%20the%20beach%20as%20workers%20move%20the%20vessel%20toward%20the%20museum.%3Cp%3EGriffin%20Museum%20of%20Science%20and%20Industry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201954%2C%20the%20U-505%20was%20towed%20from%20Portsmouth%2C%20New%20Hampshire%2C%20where%20it%20was%20being%20stored%2C%20through%2028%20locks%20and%20four%20Great%20Lakes%20to%20Chicago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20towed%203%2C000%20miles%20to%2057th%20Street%20Beach%20in%20Chicago%2C%20the%20next%20hurdle%20was%20transporting%20the%20submarine%20from%20the%20waters%20of%20Lake%20Michigan%20to%20the%20museum%20%E2%80%94%20an%20800-foot%20journey%20that%20included%20passing%20over%20an%20urban%20expressway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20a%20week%2C%20engineers%20removed%20parts%20of%20the%20sub%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20pull%2C%20then%20moved%20it%20across%20Lake%20Shore%20Drive%20using%20a%20network%20of%20rails%20and%20rollers%20to%20its%20permanent%20display%20outside%20the%20museum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20U-505's%20lair%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20U-505%20takes%20up%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20large%20exhibit.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6778299c44aa267a51f22304%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20U-505%20takes%20up%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20large%20exhibit.%3Cp%3EGriffin%20Museum%20of%20Science%20and%20Industry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20U-505%20was%20initially%20berthed%20outdoors%20but%20was%20later%20moved%20into%20an%20indoor%20climate-controlled%20environment%20to%20better%20preserve%20it%20in%20the%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lives%20and%20the%20history%20that%20is%20embedded%20within%20the%20U-505%2C%20we%20don't%20want%20to%20lose%20any%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Voula%20Saridakis%2C%20a%20curator%20at%20the%20Museum%20of%20Science%20and%20Industry%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20important%2C%20historically%2C%20of%20what%20this%20war%20was%20all%20about%2C%20especially%20the%20Battle%20of%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20which%20often%2C%20I%20think%2C%20gets%20overlooked%20in%20many%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20its%20size%2C%20the%20exhibit's%20concrete%20housing%20was%20erected%20around%20the%20U-505%2C%20surrounded%20by%20external%20exhibits%20that%20relayed%20the%20history%20of%20the%20submarine%20and%20the%20Battle%20of%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20whose%20toll%20included%20over%20100%2C000%20sailors%20and%20mariners%20and%203%2C500%20merchant%20ships%3B%20Germany%20alone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.history.navy.mil%2Fbrowse-by-topic%2Fwars-conflicts-and-operations%2Fworld-war-ii%2F1942%2Fatlantic.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%3C%2Fa%3E%20783%20U-boats%20and%20an%20estimated%2030%2C000%20crewmen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20interior%20of%20the%20submarine%20was%20meticulously%20restored%20to%20replicate%20the%20atmosphere%20and%20environment%20a