Farticles%2Fc2egdp4egl7o%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Caroline%20Darian%20has%20become%20a%20vocal%20advocate%20for%20victims%20of%20sexual%20violence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20her%20mother's%20trial.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A94%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc2egdp4egl7o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc2egdp4egl7o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fc2egdp4egl7o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chris%20nails%20Diljit's%20Punjabi%20phrase%20ahead%20of%20India%20tour%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736575346000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117139437%2Cimgsize-45814.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fcoldplays-chris-martin-nails-diljit-dosanjhs-punjabi-phrase-ahead-of-mumbai-concert-crowd-goes-wild-as-singer-says-punjabi-aa-gaye-oye%2Farticleshow%2F117138762.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F117138762.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EChris%20Martin%20spoke%20Punjabi%20during%20a%20Coldplay%20concert%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%2C%20exciting%20fans%20with%20Diljit%20Dosanjh's%20catchphrase.%20Diljit%20shared%20the%20viral%20clip%20on%20social%20media.%20Coldplay%20is%20set%20to%20perform%20in%20India%20soon%2C%20marking%20their%20return%20since%202016.%20However%2C%20the%20concert%20excitement%20faces%20controversy%20over%20ticket%20scalping%2C%20with%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20dismissing%20a%20related%20plea.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fenglish%2Fmusic%2Fnews%2Fcoldplays-chris-martin-nails-diljit-dosanjhs-punjabi-phrase-ahead-of-mumbai-concert-crowd-goes-wild-as-singer-says-punjabi-aa-gaye-oye%2Farticleshow%2F117138762.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20The%20Story%20Of%20Congress's%20'Indira%20Bhavan'%2C%20Which%20Took%2015%20Years%20To%20Complete%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20auspicious%20occasion%20of%20Makar%20Sankranti%2C%20January%2015%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20in%20her%20capacity%20as%20chairperson%20of%20the%20Congress%20Party%20in%20Parliament%20(CPP)%2C%20will%20inaugurate%20Indira%20Bhavan%2C%20the%20new%20headquarters%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Congress%20Committee%20(AICC).%20The%20event%20was%20originally%20planned%20for%20the%20party's%20Foundation%20Day%2C%20December%2028%2C%20but%20the%20death%20of%20Dr%20Manmohan%20Singh%20and%20the%20subsequent%20national%20mourning%20delayed%20the%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two-acre%20plot%20where%20the%20new%20office%20is%20located%20is%20bounded%20by%20Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyay%20Marg%20and%20Kotla%20Marg.%20To%20avoid%20having%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20stalwart%20and%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20icon%2C%20Upadhyay%2C%20the%20Congress%20in%20its%20address%20has%20chosen%20to%20position%20the%20front%20gate%20on%20Kotla%20Marg%2C%20which%20is%20essentially%20the%20rear%20of%20the%20plot.%20As%20a%20result%2C%209A%20Kotla%20Marg%20will%20become%20the%20new%20address%20of%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOriginally%20known%20as%20Rouse%20Avenue%20(named%20after%20Sir%20Alexander%20Macdonald%20Rouse%2C%20the%20superintending%20engineer%20who%20oversaw%20the%20New%20Delhi%20project%20a%20century%20ago)%2C%20the%20road%20was%20renamed%20in%201970%20after%20the%20founding%20General%20Secretary%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Jan%20Sangh%2C%20who%20built%20the%20party%20between%201953%20and%201968.%20The%20Jan%20Sangh%20had%20won%20the%201967%20local%20elections%20in%20Delhi%2C%20and%20the%20regime%20led%20by%20Vijay%20Kumar%20Malhotra%20renamed%20the%20road%20and%20placed%20a%20statue%20of%20Upadhyay%20in%20a%20park%20that%20now%20faces%20the%20swank%20headquarters%20of%20the%20BJP%20at%206A%2C%20Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyay%20Marg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Back-Door%20Entrance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20time%20the%20Congress%20has%20opted%20for%20a%20back-door%20entrance.%20Jawahar%20Bhavan%2C%20located%20on%20Dr.%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20Road%20and%20housing%20the%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20Foundation%2C%20is%20on%20a%20plot%20whose%20original%20address%20was%203%20Raisina%20Road.%20It%20was%20initially%20built%20as%20the%20AICC%20office%20but%20was%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20Foundation%20after%20Rajiv%20Gandhi's%20tragic%20assassination%20in%201991.%20The%20plot%20was%20opposite%206%20Raisina%20Road%2C%20which%20was%20then%20occupied%20by%20Opposition%20stalwart%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee.%20Thus%2C%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20chose%20the%20back-door%20entrance%20for%20the%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20parties%20and%20institutions%20are%20allocated%20plots%20for%20their%20offices%20in%20the%20Rouse%20Avenue%20area.%20The%20Gandhi%20Peace%20Foundation%2C%20where%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%20decided%20that%20Morarji%20Desai%20would%20be%20the%20Janata%20Prime%20Minister%20in%201977%2C%20is%20located%20on%20this%20road.%20Other%20offices%20here%20include%20those%20of%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20and%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK).%20Rouse%20Avenue%20is%20also%20the%20site%20of%20special%20courts%20where%20cases%20involving%20VVIPs%2C%20filed%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20and%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%2C%20are%20adjudicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(CPI)%20set%20up%20its%20headquarters%2C%20Ajoy%20Bhavan%2C%20at%2015%20Kotla%20Marg%20in%201972.%20Named%20after%20Ajoy%20Ghose%2C%20general%20secretary%20of%20the%20undivided%20CPI%2C%20the%20office%20faces%20the%20site%20of%20the%20original%20Central%20Jail%20of%20Delhi%2C%20which%20was%20relocated%20to%20Tihar%20in%201957.%20An%20adjacent%20bungalow%20was%20used%20in%20the%201950s%20to%20incarcerate%20Sheikh%20Mohammad%20Abdullah%20of%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir.%20The%20CPI%20was%20India's%20principal%20opposition%20party%20until%201967%2C%20but%20its%20prominence%20faded%20in%20the%20seventies%20as%20it%20moved%20to%20Kotla%20Marg.%20Today%2C%20CPI%20has%20two%20MPs%20each%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Beginning%20With%20Anand%20Bhavan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20headquarters%2C%20which%20will%20celebrate%20its%20140th%20anniversary%20in%20December%202025%2C%20begins%20in%201930%2C%20when%20Motilal%20Nehru%20built%20Anand%20Bhavan%20in%20Allahabad%20(now%20Prayagraj).%20His%20previous%20home%2C%20adjacent%20to%20Anand%20Bhavan%20and%20later%20renamed%20Swaraj%20Bhavan%2C%20was%20dedicated%20to%20the%20nation%20and%20became%20the%20office%20of%20the%20AICC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201931%2C%20the%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20(CWC)%20at%20Swaraj%20Bhavan%20included%20four%20members%20from%20the%20Nehru%20family%3A%20Motilal%20Nehru%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20Kamla%20Nehru%2C%20and%20Motilal's%20son-in-law%2C%20Ranjit%20Sitaram%20Pandit%20(husband%20of%20Vijay%20Laxmi%20Pandit%2C%20Jawaharlal's%20sister).%20As%20the%20party%20moves%20into%20Indira%20Bhavan%20in%202025%2C%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20and%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%20will%20be%20part%20of%20the%20CWC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AICC%20office%20moved%20to%20New%20Delhi%20in%201947%2C%20just%20before%20Independence.%20The%20CWC%20deliberated%20on%20the%20Partition%20Plan%20at%20its%20new%20office%2C%207%20Jantar%20Mantar%20Road%2C%20on%20June%2015%2C%201947.%20This%20office%20was%20extensively%20used%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20for%20party%20work.%20In%201959%2C%20when%20Indira%20Gandhi%20became%20Congress%20President%2C%207%20Jantar%20Mantar%20Road%20became%20her%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistory%20Of%20Shifting%20Addresses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Congress%20split%20in%201969%2C%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20supporters%20requisitioning%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Congress%20Committee%20(AICC)%2C%20the%20official%20party%2C%20led%20by%20S.%20Nijalingappa%20and%20referred%20to%20as%20Congress%20(Organisation)%2C%20retained%20control%20over%207%20Jantar%20Mantar%20Road.%20In%201977%2C%20the%20merger%20of%20the%20Congress%20(O)%20into%20the%20Janata%20Party%20led%20to%20the%20Janata%20Party%20headquarters%20being%20located%20at%20these%20premises.%20After%20a%20series%20of%20splits%20in%20the%20Janata%20movement%2C%20the%20current%20occupants%20of%20the%20office%20include%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20(JD-U)%2C%20along%20with%20commercial%20entities%20such%20as%20Rentokil%20Pest%20Control%20and%20Antim%20Yatra%20Funeral%20Service.%20Ownership%20of%207%20Jantar%20Mantar%20Road%2C%20as%20per%20a%20notification%20in%201993%2C%20now%20lies%20with%20the%20Central%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%201969%20split%2C%20%C2%A0the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20faction%20of%20the%20Congress%20held%20its%20session%20at%20Mavlankar%20Hall%2C%20with%20Jagjivan%20Ram%20presiding.%20In%201971%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20recognised%20the%20party%2C%20which%20swept%20the%20polls%2C%20as%20Congress%20(Jagjivan).%20Two%20bungalows%20on%20nearby%20Raisina%20Road%E2%80%943%20and%205%E2%80%94were%20used%20for%20ancillary%20events%20during%20the%201969%20session.%20These%20two%20bungalows%20later%20became%20part%20of%20the%20AICC%20setup%2C%20although%20the%20party%20headquarters%20remained%20at%2021%20Windsor%20Place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AICC%20subsequently%20moved%20to%205%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20Road%2C%20which%20had%20been%20occupied%20by%20Morarji%20Desai%20as%20Deputy%20Prime%20Minister%20until%201969%2C%20when%20he%20quit%20the%20Indira%20government%20after%20the%20split.%205%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20Road%20saw%20both%20the%20triumph%20of%20the%201971%20poll%20victory%20and%20the%20dark%20days%20of%20the%20Emergency.%20Dr.%20Shankar%20Dayal%20Sharma%20and%20D.K.%20Barooah%20presided%20over%20the%20party%20during%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%201978%20Split%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20faced%20yet%20another%20split%20in%20January%201978%2C%20and%20the%20party%20led%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20moved%20to%20its%20current%20premises%20at%2024%20Akbar%20Road%2C%20adjacent%20to%2010%20Janpath.%20Now%20the%20residence%20of%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20this%20bungalow%20had%20previously%20served%20as%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Indian%20Youth%20Congress%20during%20the%20tenure%20of%20Ambika%20Soni%20as%20president%2C%20with%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%20as%20its%20most%20powerful%20National%20Council%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20the%201978%20split%20is%20fascinating.%20When%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20S.L.%20Shakhder%20adjudicated%20the%20split%2C%20he%20recognised%20the%20faction%20led%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Creal%20Congress%E2%80%9D%2C%20entitled%20to%20function%20under%20the%20name%20and%20style%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress.%20Shakhder%20noted%20that%20the%20other%20faction%20had%20seen%20many%20exits%20and%20entries.%20For%20instance%2C%20K.%20Brahmananda%20Reddy%2C%20who%20had%20been%20elected%20Congress%20President%20in%20May%201977%20and%20headed%20the%20party%20against%20which%20Indira%20Gandhi%20revolted%20in%201978%2C%20later%20joined%20Congress%20(I).%20Devraj%20Urs%2C%20one%20of%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20lieutenants%20in%201978%2C%20was%20heading%20the%20opposing%20faction%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20adjudication.%20V.M.%20Syed%20Mohammed%2C%20the%20lawyer%20who%20initially%20represented%20the%20%E2%80%98other%20Congress'%20in%20the%20case%2C%20had%20crossed%20over%20to%20Indira's%20party%20and%20had%20been%20appointed%20High%20Commissioner%20in%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShakhder%20forbade%20the%20%E2%80%98other%20Congress'%20from%20styling%20itself%20as%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20and%20assigned%20it%20the%20name%20Indian%20Congress%20(Socialist).%20Later%2C%20Sharad%20Pawar%20headed%20that%20party%2C%20which%20merged%20with%20the%20main%20Congress%20party%20in%20December%201985%20at%20a%20rally%20in%20Nagpur.%20This%20merger%20resulted%20in%203%20Raisina%20Road%2C%20which%20had%20been%20the%20headquarters%20of%20Congress%20(S)%2C%20being%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20parent%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJawahar%20Bhavan%2C%20located%20on%20the%20plot%20of%20the%20original%203%20Raisina%20Road%2C%20housed%20extension%20offices%20of%20the%20AICC%20until%20May%201991.%20Among%20its%20occupants%20was%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%2C%20who%20headed%20the%20party's%20communications%20and%20other%20departments%20during%20the%201991%20elections.%20Jitendra%20Prasada%2C%20political%20secretary%20to%20the%20then%20Congress%20President%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20also%20used%20the%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20last%2C%20the%20AICC%20will%20have%20its%20own%20premises%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20The%20foundation%20stone%20of%20Indira%20Bhavan%20was%20laid%20by%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20as%20Congress%20President%2C%20on%20the%20party's%20125th%20anniversary%20in%20December%202009.%20The%20project%20took%2015%20years%20to%20come%20to%20fruition.%20Work%20on%20the%20nearby%20BJP%20national%20headquarters%20at%206A%20Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyay%20Marg%20began%20in%20August%202016%2C%20was%20completed%20in%2018%20months%2C%20and%20the%20inauguration%20was%20held%20in%20February%202018.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shubhabrata%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20retired%20editor%20and%20a%20public%20affairs%20commentator)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736575320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fm1edesbg_indira-bhavan_625x300_11_January_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-story-of-congresss-indira-bhavan-which-took-15-years-to-complete-7444318%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20last%2C%20the%20AICC%20will%20have%20its%20own%20premises%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20The%20foundation%20stone%20of%20Indira%20Bhavan%20was%20laid%20by%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20as%20Congress%20President%2C%20on%20the%20partys%20125th%20anniversary%20in%20December%202009.%20The%20project%20took%2015%20years%20to%20come%20to%20fruition.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fthe-story-of-congresss-indira-bhavan-which-took-15-years-to-complete-7444318%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20picks%20Bill%20Briggs%20as%20deputy%20administrator%20of%20US%20small%20business%20administration%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736575024000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-117139504%2Cimgsize-587685.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-picks-bill-briggs-as-deputy-administrator-of-us-small-business-administration%2Farticleshow%2F117138961.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F117138961.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20appointed%20Bill%20Briggs%20as%20the%20deputy%20administrator%20of%20the%20small%20business%20administration%20for%20his%20second%20term.%20Briggs%2C%20who%20previously%20oversaw%20the%20Paycheck%20Protection%20Program%2C%20will%20work%20with%20Kelly%20Loeffler%20to%20support%20small%20businesses%2C%20which